(\Omega, \mathcal{F}, (\mathcal{F}_t), \mathbb{P} )
 t \in \mathbb{R}_+
X =(X_t)_{t\geq0}
\mathcal{F}_t
 \forall n \in \mathbb{N}, \quad  X_n (t, \omega)= \sum_{k\geq0} X_{\frac{k}{2^n }}(\omega) \mathbf{1}_{\left[\frac{k}{2^n }, \frac{k+1}{2^n }\right)} (t)
X_n (t, \omega)\underset{n \rightarrow \infty} {\overset{w-a.e.}{\longrightarrow }} X(t, \omega) 
(X_n (t, \omega))_{n\in \mathbb{N}}
t\in\mathbb{R}_+\longmapsto X_n (t, \omega)
